# Frontend Rules

## API Calls
- Never call `fetch()` or any HTTP client directly inside a component.
- All API calls go through `client/src/lib/api.ts`, which wraps fetch with base URL and error handling.
- Components consume data via React Query hooks only. Hooks are defined in `features/*/hooks/` or `hooks/`.

## Components
- Every component must export a typed `Props` interface. No inline prop types, no `any`.
- No inline styles. Tailwind utility classes only.
- Keep components focused: a component should do one thing. Extract sub-components when a component grows beyond ~100 lines.

## State Management
- Server state (API data, loading, error): React Query only.
- Global UI state (modals, toasts, nav open): Zustand only.
- Local, non-shared UI state: `useState` / `useReducer`.
- Never store server data in Zustand. Never store UI-only state in React Query.

## Zustand
- Store files live in `client/src/store/`.
- One store per concern (e.g. `ui.ts` for nav/modal state).

## Imports
- Use the `@/` alias for all src-relative imports: `import { Button } from '@/components/ui'`.
- Never use relative `../../` imports that traverse more than one directory up.

## Forms
- Validate form inputs with Zod schemas (mirroring server schemas) before calling the mutation.
